<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF Officer on Cooperation With Palestinians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Officer on Cooperation With Palestinians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1406130794 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0830 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1406130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brigadier General Yom-Tov Sami', head of the 
Israeli-Palestinian liaison committee, says that the joint IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] and Palestinian police headquarters have 
proven themselves a great success. Sami' said the security 
situation in the autonomous areas is satisfactory, and voiced 
optimism concerning the Gaza-Jericho agreement. He added, 
however, that unless the economic situation in the Gaza Strip 
improves, the security situation could deteriorate. Our 
correspondent Geva' Qra'-'Oz reports that Brig. Gen. Sami' 
divulged that in the framework of their preparations for Yasir 
'Arafat's arrival in the Gaza Strip, the Palestinians have 
started preparing a helicopter landing pad in Gaza, despite the 
fact that they are not authorized to do so. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

