<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Entry Ban Eased for Palestinian Women, Children </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Entry Ban Eased for Palestinian Women, Children </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1206053694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 12 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1206053694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Police Minister Moshe Shahal has announced that 
Palestinian women, regardless of age, and youths up to 16 years 
old can enter Israel freely again. The move eased an entry ban 
imposed on Palestinians from the territories following the wave 
of bombings in early April. Shahal said he hoped the move would 
lead to a return of normal life but this would depend on the 
Palestinian side. 
  A Qol Yisra'el reporter adds that despite the closure of the 
territories, police have been arresting several hundred 
Palestinians weekly for illegal entry into Israel. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

