<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin on PLO Control of Autonomy, Talks With Syria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin on PLO Control of Autonomy, Talks With Syria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1406045494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 14 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1406045494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin says Israel is waiting 
for PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat to assume control in Gaza and 
Jericho before it continues negotiations with the PLO. The 
prime minister spoke at a news conference in Haifa last night. 
Sylvia Leaf reports: 
  [Begin recording] [Leaf] Yasir 'Arafat will be allowed to 
enter Gaza and Jericho whenever he wishes, Prime Minister Rabin 
told reporters, but he must also assume responsibility over the 
Palestinian authorities. 
  [Rabin] At this stage, I am focusing to see how the PLO, 
through the Palestinian Authority, succeed to take over and to 
control, in accordance to their commitment to us on the DOP 
[Document of Principles] and the Cairo agreement, to fulfill 
their parts. Before that, I will not pass any judgment. 
  [Leaf] Regarding a peace agreement with Syria, the prime 
minister said the Syrians believe that America can influence 
Israel against her will, and this attitude won't succeed. He 
stressed that solutions can be found only when agreed upon by 
both Israel and Syria. 
  The prime minister said the recent closure of the 
territories 
to Arab workers has resulted in the employment of a further 
25,000 Israelis in the building industry. Justifying his 
authorization of work permits for 25,000 Palestinians from the 
territories, Rabin pointed out that in the past year, no 
terrorist attacks have been carried out in Israel by 
Palestinians permitted to work here. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

