<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India will support China's reentry into the General 
Agreement on Tariffs and Trade, GATT, as this will ensure 
enhanced growth in trade. The commerce minister, Mr. Pranab 
Mukherji, said this while addressing the India-China Joint Group 
meeting on economic relations, trade, and science and technology 
in New Delhi today. Mr. Mukherji said New Delhi shares the 
Chinese view that improvement in trade position should benefit 
