<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Salih Receives GCC Ambassadors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Salih Receives GCC Ambassadors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1506130594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1506130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman, today received the ambassadors of 
the Gulf Cooperation Council [GCC] member states to our country. 
The president asked the ambassadors to convey messages to his 
brothers the leaders of these states on developments in our 
country and issues concerning relations between our country and 
each of their states. 
  In his messages, the brother president stressed that what is 
going on in Yemen is an internal affair in which no party should 
interfere in order to ensure that the conflict will not be 
prolonged and to spare further Yemeni blood. The brother 
president urged his brothers the leaders of the GCC member 
states to do whatever is needed to preserve the Yemeni unity and 
stability in Yemen which will be in the interest of the Yemeni 
people and strengthen security and stability in the region. He 
stressed that the Yemeni unity is an important and basic element 
for stability in Yemen and the region and embodies the Arab 
nation's national objectives and supreme interests. He also 
stressed that preserving this unity is a pan- Arab 
responsibility as much as a Yemeni responsibility. 
  The brother leader noted the Republic of Yemen's eagerness 
to 
improve its strong brotherly ties with its sisterly GCC member 
states on the basis of mutual respect, good neighborliness, 
noninterference in internal affairs, and the positive 
cooperation that embodies the common aspirations of the Yemeni 
people and their brothers in the Arabian Peninsula and the Gulf. 

</TEXT>

