<H3> <TI>   House Urges Distribution of Stockpiled Food </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House Urges Distribution of Stockpiled Food </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1506140294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1506140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The House of Representatives held an ordinary 
session this morning under Brother Dr. 'Abd-al-Wahhab Mahmud, 
member of the House's Speakership Office. 
  At the outset of the session, the people's deputies reviewed 
and ratified the minutes of the previous session after urging 
and appealing to the government agencies to transport and 
distribute the basic food commodities available in large 
quantities at ports, mills, warehouses, and silos. These 
commodities, the House stressed, must be distributed to citizens 
in all governorates of the Republic of Yemen, and merchants and 
the public and private food suppliers must sell the commodities 
hoarded in their houses to the citizens at the official prices. 
