<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Warns Against Price Tampering </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Warns Against Price Tampering </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1506180994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1506180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Council of Ministers held its periodic 
meeting this morning under the chairmanship of Acting Prime 
Minister Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar. The council discussed 
several issues listed on its en TMF1 including the supply issue. 
After reviewing ideas on how to deal with supply problems in a 
radical and successful way, the council decided to task the 
Economic Council with working out ways to deal with the issue in 
an accurate manner after assessing all [word indistinct]. 
  The Council of Ministers has recently noticed that a number 
of merchants are tampering with prices and exploiting the 
current situation in the country to tamper with citizens' food. 
Therefore, the government appeals to every one to shoulder his 
responsibility under the country's current circumstances imposed 
by the [word indistinct] homeland. 
  The government, at same time, warns against raising or 
tampering with prices, and considers such behavior an economic 
crime, the most serious of which is involvement in hoarding 
commodities. The council sent cables to the Ministry of Supply 
and Trade, the Ministry of Interior, the public prosecutor, the 
security forces, and all competent authorities to take deterrent 
measures against tamperers. 
  The council also expects the brother citizens to cooperate 
with these institutions and to inform the competent authorities 
of anyone tampering with prices. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

