<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Jun 16--Eyewitnesses have reported that a 
northern fighter plane attempted this morning to shell the house 
of 'Ali Salim al-Bid, secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist 
Party [YSP], in the suburb of Kuraitar, the largest suburb of 
Aden. 
  The witnesses added that the plane fired one of its missiles 
at the house of al-Bid, who is currently in Hadramawt 
governorate. They said that ground defenses fired at the plane, 
forcing it to flee. 
  The extent of damage to al-Bid's house as a result of the 
incident was not immediately known. 

