<H3> <TI>   Northern Planes Reportedly Bomb Aden Airport </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Planes Reportedly Bomb Aden Airport </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1606094494 Paris AFP in English 0918 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1606094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 16 (AFP)--Northern Yemeni 
warplanes dodged southern anti-aircraft fire to bomb Aden 
airport on Thursday, damaging hangers there, an AFP 
correspondent reported. 
  A huge plume of smoke rose above the airport in the southern 
stronghold as ambulances raced to the scene, following the air 
raid late morning. 
  There were no immediate details of casualties or the extent 
of the damage. 
  Northern forces loyal to President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
besieging the key port city of Aden for three weeks, have 
targeted the airport several times to stop southern jet planes 
from taking off there. 
  Meanwhile, northern artillery units continued to fire shells 
sporadically at Aden following a dawn attack on the northern 
suburb of Shaykh 'Uthman which hospital officials said killed at 
least 18 civilians and wounded several more. 

</TEXT>

