<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-116 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres Denies Agreement on 'Arafat Jerusalem Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres Denies Agreement on 'Arafat Jerusalem Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1606100994 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 16 Jun 94 p A1 </F>
<F P=103> TA1606100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Nadav Shragay, Gid'on Alon, Eytan Rabin, and Aluf </F>
Ben] 
  [Excerpts] "Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres and PLO 
chairman Yasir 'Arafat agreed in their meeting in Bucharest two 
weeks before the Cairo agreement was signed that 'Arafat would 
visit Temple Mount," Palestinian sources said yesterday. 
  According to these sources, the agreement was preceded by 
exhausting negotiations in which 'Arafat repeatedly raised his 
request to visit Jerusalem escorted by armed Palestinian 
policemen. The Israelis initially refused his request, but 
finally agreed to allow 'Arafat to hold a ceremonial visit to 
Temple Mount, perhaps even accompanied by flag-bearing 
Palestinian policemen. 
  Peres stated yesterday that Israel had not received a 
request 
from 'Arafat to visit Jerusalem. "We do not rush to give 
answers to unasked questions," said Peres, who is currently 
visiting Ukraine. Sources in his entourage noted that to the 
best of their knowledge the reports about an agreement reached 
between Peres and 'Arafat during their meeting in Bucharest 
concerning the PLO chairman visiting Jerusalem escorted by 
flag-bearing Palestinian policemen are not true. [passage 
omitted] 
  Security sources noted yesterday that Jibril al-Rujub, head 
of the Palestinian secret service in the territories whose 
activities have been confined to the Jericho area, visited East 
Jerusalem and the Old City on several occasions over the past 
few weeks. The sources expressed their concern about this 
occurrence, noting that these visits might cause security 
damage. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

