<H3> <TI>   PRC Assistant Foreign Minister Arrives in Baghdad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Assistant Foreign Minister Arrives in Baghdad </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With 'Aziz </H4>

<F P=102> JN1506202694 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1911 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1506202694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 15 Jun (INA) -- Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 
'Aziz received PRC Assistant Foreign Minister Wang Changyi and 
the delegation accompanying him today. 
  During the meeting, the deputy prime minister gave a 
detailed 
explanation on the development of the relationship between Iraq 
and the UN Security Council, and Iraq's intensive efforts to end 
the unjust embargo that was imposed on it even after it has 
implemented the obligations that were asked of it. 'Aziz said 
that now that Iraq has fulfilled its obligations, the UN 
Security Council should also fulfill its obligations toward 
Iraq. Tariq 'Aziz praised the PRC's positive role in this 
respect. 
  Tariq 'Aziz stressed the need for the PRC, as a UN Security 
Council permanent member, to exercise an effective role by 
supporting Iraq's legitimate demands to end the unjust embargo 
after its causes have been eliminated. 
  During the meeting the two sides discussed friendship and 
cooperation between Iraq and the PRC and ways of enhancing them 
in service of the two friendly countries and people. 

</TEXT>

