  [Text] Baghdad, 16 Jun (TANJUG) -- Milorad Unkovic, federal 
minister for foreign economic relations, arrived in Baghdad this 
morning. He is heading a Yugoslav delegation during its 
official visit to Iraq at the invitation of the Iraqi 
Government. In the course of his visit, scheduled to end on 
Monday, Unkovic will meet a number of high-ranking Iraqi 
officials. 
  He is expected to discuss bilateral relations and 
particularly economic problems and outstanding debts owed to 
Yugoslav companies which have for years been involved in 
construction projects. The projects and the payments for them 
were suspended after Iraqi troops entered Kuwait in August 1991. 

