<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 8 Jun (INA)--Sa'di Jalshar [name as 
received], Turkey's charge d'affaires in Baghdad, has said that 
mid-June will see the implementation of the Turkish Government's 
decision to resume trade activities with Iraq through al-Khabur 
border post. 
  AL-JUMHURIYAH today reports that Jalshar's assertions were 
made during a meeting with National Assembly Speaker Sa'di Mahdi 
Salih. He also said that Turkey will implement its decision 
after completing all the necessary measures by the Turkish 
Finance Ministry and Turkish customs authorities. 
  The Turkish charge d'affaires added that officials in his 
country are holding intensive contacts with the UN Security 
Council permanent members to arrive at a common understanding to 
implement the two agreements which Ankara and Baghdad reached on 
the reopening of the Iraqi-Turkish oil pipeline. 
  He noted that the foreign relations committee in his 
country's parliament asked Osdom Sanirk [name as received], the 
Turkish Foreign Ministry under secretary, to provide detailed 
information on his recent visit to Baghdad and the successful 
talks he held with Iraqi officials in (?April). 

