<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iraq has protested to the Arab League against the 
continued violation of its airspace by the U.S., British, and 
French aircraft flying from bases in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait, 
noting that this poses a serious threat to Iraq's security, 
sovereignty, and national unity. 
  In a letter addressed to Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid, Arab 
League secretary general, Iraq's permanent representative to the 
Arab League said these aircraft continued their violation of 
Iraqi airspace during the period 1-8 June, carrying out 462 
aggressive sorties. 
  Iraq's representative asked that the letter, along with the 
list detailing these violations, be circulated to the Arab 
member states. 

