<H3> <TI>   Minister: State Subsidizing 99.7 Percent of Food </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister: State Subsidizing 99.7 Percent of Food </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1406142694 Baghdad AL-THAWRAH in Arabic 1 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1406142694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-THAWRAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Trade Minister Dr. Muhammad Mahdi Salih has told the 
Iraqi News Agency that the assistance provided by the state in 
accordance with the directives of leader President Saddam 
Husayn, may God preserve and protect him, in order to ensure 
food for the citizens at symbolic prices amounts to 99.7 percent 
of the cost of the foodstuffs that Iraqi families receive under 
the ration card. 
  The minister added: The official price of the foodstuffs 
that are given to every individual under the ration card is 
3.085 dinars, while their market price is 1,015 dinars. Thus 
the state pays the difference of 1,012 dinars for every 
individual. The official price of milk and the other materials 
such as soaps and washing powders given to children below one 
year is 3.400 dinars, while the market price is 700 dinars. 
Thus, the state pays a difference in price of 697 dinars. 

</TEXT>

