<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-116 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Citizens Urged To Ration Electricity Consumption </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Citizens Urged To Ration Electricity Consumption </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1606081994 Baghdad AL-THAWRAH in Arabic 12 Jun 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> JN1606081994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-THAWRAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Industry and Minerals has emphasized 
that its technical and engineering cadres specialized in the 
electrical sector are doing their best to ensure that electrical 
current reaches all parts of the country. 
  Subhi Nijm al-'Ani, director general of the Electricity 
Department said that ensuring constant electrical current 
depends on citizens' cooperation with the technical organs 
through rationing consumption of electrical power and avoiding 
unnecessary consumption or unjustified extravagance. 
  He said such intentional extravagance in electricity 
consumption includes switching on a large number of lights in 
gardens and houses, which wastes a great deal of energy and 
encroaches on the rights of others. 
  He said the best type of light for rationing electricity is 
the neon light because it consumes less energy and gives more 
light. 

</TEXT>

