<H3> <TI>   Musa Leaves for Malta on Three-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Leaves for Malta on Three-Day Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1506113994 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1000 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1506113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa left Tunis this morning 
for Malta on a three-day official visit after participating in 
the African summit meetings. In a predeparture statement, he 
said that President Mubarak's participation in the African 
summit and his inaugural speech played an extremely important 
role in advancing efforts toward resolving African problems. 
These efforts were in completion of Egypt's tasks during its 
chairmanship of the OAU. He said that Egypt presented proposals 
and held consultations that were welcomed and appreciated by all 
delegations. They contributed significantly towards resolving 
problems discussed during the summit, particularly the issues of 
development and debts. 
  Musa said that his visit to Malta is within the framework of 
cooperation among the Mediterranean countries and preparation 
for a meeting among a number of those countries' foreign 
ministers to study the situation in the region and coordinate 
policies. He noted he will also discuss ways of bolstering ties 
between Egypt and Malta in all fields. 

</TEXT>

