<H3> <TI>   Ministry To End Production Tax Exemptions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry To End Production Tax Exemptions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506185094 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506185094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tax relief for 60 percent of the country's economic 
activities will be cancelled in the second five-year economic 
development plan. 
  According to Economics and Finance Minister Morteza 
Mohammad-Khan the above mentioned activities currently include 
water, electricity, gas, communications, oil, and other sectors 
currently tax exempt. All such tax exemptions are to be scrapped 
according to the second development plan. 
  Mohammad-Khan stated that oil revenue constitutes the 
country's highest source of income. He said: Tax incomes are 
very low in comparison; during the past five years the country's 
economy has moved from a disorderly and irregular situation to a 
disciplined, steady, and structured economy. 

</TEXT>

