<F P=103> LD1506083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It has been officially announced in Rabat that 
Morocco has again rejected any OAU participation in carrying out 
the self-determination referendum in the Western Sahara, which 
the United Nations has set for the end of 1994. 
  This confirmation came after the Moroccan Government 
received 
a message from the UN secretary general in which he informed 
Morocco of the appointment of two OAU representatives charged 
with the task of monitoring the work of the voter identification 
commission for the people invited to participate in the 
elections. 

</TEXT>

