<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th Meets With Gazan Police, Security Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th Meets With Gazan Police, Security Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1506195494 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 15 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1506195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, official in charge of the 
international portfolio, held a series of meetings at the 
headquarters of the Palestinian Authority in the city of Gaza 
last night. He met with the commanders of the Palestinian 
police, as well as the head of the Palestinian security forces 
in the Strip to acquaint himself with problems facing the 
Palestinian security force since its deployment in the self-rule 
area. 
  Dr. Sha'th had arrived in Gaza last night. He told 
Journalists that he was carrying an amount of money to pay the 
salaries of the employees of the Palestinian Authority's 
self-rule and policemen. 
  He added he would prepare for the arrival of brother 
President Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] in the Palestinian 
self-rule area. 

</TEXT>

