<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Official Denies Saudis Finance Movement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Official Denies Saudis Finance Movement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1506191494 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 15 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1506191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Basim Abu-Sumayyah in "the occupied territories"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Dr. Mahmud al-Zahhar, a Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement] official in Gaza, has stated that Israeli officials' 
statements that the Hamas movement receives funds from Saudi 
Arabia are groundless slander to bring pressure to bear on Saudi 
Arabia. In reply to a question by Radio Monte Carlo, al-Zahhar 
said that Saudi Arabia, as a government, has not offered any 
financial assistance to the Hamas Movement. Al-Zahhar said that 
Saudi Arabia is committed to the Arab stand of supporting the 
PLO. 
  Al-Zahhar explained that Hamas receives donations from 
private persons as Zakat [alms tax] funds, which are collected 
from Muslims and offered to the mujahidin in all parts of the 
world. These also include donations to the poor, and to the 
families of martyrs and detainees. He said that these donations 
are received from many countries, not just from Saudi Arabia and 
are not government funds. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

