<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Asfur Expelled From Palestinian People's Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Asfur Expelled From Palestinian People's Party </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1606112394 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 16 Jun 94 p A4 </F>
<F P=103> TA1606112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Gaza correspondent 'Amira Hess] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Hasan 'Asfur, a leader of the 
Palestinian People's Party (formerly the Communist Party) and a 
senior participant in the negotiations for the Declaration of 
Principles and the Cairo agreement, was expelled from the 
party's ranks in a special session of the central committee held 
in the West Bank earlier this week. According to party members, 
the decision came "due to 'Asfur's role in the negotiations that 
led to the Cairo agreement on 4 May, an agreement repudiated by 
the party." 
  'Asfur's membership in the central committee had been frozen 
in the past few months due to his participation in the Cairo 
talks. Upon returning to the Gaza Strip after a 26-year absence, 
'Asfur, a resident of 'Abasan, was appointed as supervisor of 
the civilian and military talks. 
  The communique issued by the central committee reiterates 
the 
party's opposition to take part in the self-government. 
Following the signing of the Cairo agreement, senior party 
members in the Gaza Strip had been pushing to join the 
Palestinian Authority institutions "in order to promote 
democratization," although "this runs counter to the Palestinian 
People's Party's official line, whereby we should not 
participate in any official institution of the self-rule 
authority." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

