<H3> <TI>   Spokesman: Contact With UN on Kashmir Incidents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman: Contact With UN on Kashmir Incidents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1506155394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1506155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has established contact with the United 
Nations on increasing aggressive Indian activities along the 
Line of Control [LOC] in Kashmir. A Foreign Office spokesman 
said in Islamabad today that Pakistan condemns India's 
aggressive action against UN observers deployed along the LOC. 
The spokesman also expressed concern over the statement by 
Rajesh Pilot, Indian minister of state for external affairs 
[position as heard], about the use of helicopter gunships 
against the Kashmiri people in the occupied territories. The 
spokesman said that it might escalate to a dangerous level the 
Indian campaign of atrocities in occupied Kashmir. He said that 
India should not forget what happened in Afghanistan. 

</TEXT>

