<F P=100> OPEC Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministers Agree To Maintain Oil Production Ceiling </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministers Agree To Maintain Oil Production Ceiling </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506181294 Paris AFP in English 1719 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1506181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, June 15 (AFP) -- OPEC oil ministers agreed 
Wednesday [15 June] to maintain the organization's production 
ceiling unchanged at 24.52 million barrels a day (MBD), Libya's 
oil minister 'Abdallah Salim al-Badri said. 
  OPEC Secretary-General Subroto said the organization did not 
plan any more meetings before next November 16. 
  The ministers are slated to continue talks Thursday morning 
on choice of a new secretary-general. 
  On another point, Subroto said the ministers had decided to 
keep OPEC headquarters in Vienna, despite having received 
proposals from the city of Geneva, Switzerland, to house the 
organization's secretariat. 
  Subroto said that OPEC members had respected their quotas in 
May to a "satisfactory" extent, and that prouction for the month 
averaged 24.922 million barrels. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

