<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   King's Adviser: Rabat Boycotting OAU Meetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King's Adviser: Rabat Boycotting OAU Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506133294 Rabat MAP in English 1319 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat MAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jeddah, June 15 (MAP) -- Morocco will maintain its 
boycott of the meetings of the Organisation of African Unity 
(OAU) as long as the `Polisario' [Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Saquia El Hamra and Rio de Oro] continues to seat 
[as received] there, said Ahmed Bensouda, adviser to King Hassan 
II of Morocco. 
  In a statement published Tuesday by Saudi daily `UKAZ', 
Bensouda said Morocco did not attend any OAU meeting since the 
admission of the 'Polisario' and is still upholding its stands. 
The so-called Polisario is bustling to hamper the holding of 
the referendum in the Moroccan Sahara and wants a referendum 
that fits its interests, said Bensouda recalling that several 
members of the `Polisario' had joined Morocco, for they know 
that the Sahara is Moroccan. 
  On Morocco's relations with Arab countries, Ahmed Bensouda 
said King Hassan II is endeavoring along with Arab heads of 
state to clear up the Arab atmosphere and preserve Arab 
resources and capacities. 

</TEXT>

