<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bhutto on Threat From `Inimical' Neighbor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bhutto on Threat From `Inimical' Neighbor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0806160194 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0806160194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto has appealed to the 
religious scholars and believers in different schools of thought 
to maintain utmost discipline and caution and foil the nefarious 
designs of inimical forces by observing Muharramul Haram [holy 
month of Muharram] in a peaceful and orderly manner. 
  She was addressing the 14th annual Hussainia Conference in 
Islambad today. The prime minister said the government has 
undeniable proof of a conspiracy hatched by an inimical 
neighboring country to inject or hire citizens or some saboteurs 
so as to create law and order problems by airing harsh sectarian 
feelings [sentence as heard]. The government is alive and alert 
to its duties and would take firm measures to maintaining smooth 
law and order. She said the chief ministers of the provinces 
have already been directed to adopt stringent steps in this 
regard. In its bid to cow down Pakistan to desist from venting 
a principled moral and diplomatic support to the consensus 
Kashmir cause [as heard], the neighboring country has hatched 
conspiracies one after the other to create internal problems for 
Pakistan. The prime minister said with the help and support of 
the people and by making use of all machinery at its command the 
government would frustrate such nefarious designs. 

</TEXT>

