<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   $110-Million World Bank Loan for Potable Water Systems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    $110-Million World Bank Loan for Potable Water Systems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706091094 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 0800 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A $110-million loan agreement between the World Bank 
and Algeria was signed in Washington by Algerian Ambassador [to 
the United States] Noreddine Zerhouni and Daniel Richie, 
director of the Maghreb Department at the World Bank. 
  This agreement, which was approved by the World Bank board, 
will finance in hard currency the acquisition of technical 
equipment to modernize the drinking water systems in the 
following towns: Oran, Annaba, Ain Timouchent, Bejaia, Jijel, 
Mascra, Relizane, Setif, Sidi Bel Abbes, and Tlemcen. 

</TEXT>

