<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Cooperation Talks With Yugoslav Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economic Cooperation Talks With Yugoslav Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606205394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2014 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 16 Jun (TANJUG) -- Iraq and Yugoslavia 
today expressed their commitment -- during the hardships 
currently faced by both countries -- to finding mutually useful 
solutions for problems in their current cooperation and its 
development, when the conditions for it are ripe. 
  This is a brief summary of the talks held in Baghdad this 
afternoon between Milorad Unkovic, minister of the Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia for economic relations with foreign 
countries and Iraqi Trade Minister Muhammad Mahdi Salih. This 
meeting opened a several-day-long session of a joint 
Yugoslav-Iraqi committee for economic and technical development. 
  The aim of the session is to review the cooperation so far 
and establish the total outstanding claims of Yugoslav companies 
in Iraq. 
  In addition to the federal Yugoslav minister, the talks are 
being attended by FRY Deputy Foreign Minister Radoslav Bulajic, 
and Jovan Kostic, the charge d'affaires of the FRY Embassy in 
Baghdad, as well as a group of directors of large Yugoslav 
companies whose firms have carried out work in Iraq. 
  The Yugoslav delegation is expected to hold talks with 
senior 
Iraqi economic and state leaders over the next few days. 

</TEXT>

