<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Sources Reveal Contents of Rabin Letter to 'Arafat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Sources Reveal Contents of Rabin Letter to 'Arafat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1606183294 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1606183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin has notified PLO 
Chairman Yasir 'Arafat that the dialogue between them will go on 
in order to continue the implementation of the agreements 
between Israel and the PLO. Our political correspondent Gadi 
Sukenik has learned from sources in the PLO that this remark was 
made in a personal letter Rabin sent to 'Arafat yesterday 
morning. The letter was taken to Tunis by Jamil al-Tarifi. 
  The letter is warmly worded and in it, Rabin expresses his 
commitment to the peace process and to cooperation with 'Arafat. 
In the letter, Mr. Rabin also expresses a commitment to help 
the autonomy settle in, but it does not contain any financial 
commitment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

