<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reinforcement of IDF Troops in Jordan Valley </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reinforcement of IDF Troops in Jordan Valley </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1606113394 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 16 Jun 94 p A4 </F>
<F P=103> TA1606113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by military correspondent Eytan Rabin] </F>
  [Excerpts] Two days ago, Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin 
instructed Major General Ilan Biran, commander of the Central 
Command, to reinforce the presence of IDF [Israel Defense 
Forces] troops in the Jordan Valley, particularly in the 
vicinity of Jericho, in order to step up the security of the 
settlements in the area. [passage omitted] 
  A government source said that at Rabin's instructions the 
soldiers will help guard the settlements and prevent 
infiltrations. "If it is necessary, the soldiers will also give 
chase to infiltrators," the source added. [passage omitted] 
  There were several incidents in the territories yesterday. 
Two Palestinians were hit by rubber bullets in clashes with IDF 
troops in Hebron and Ramallah. Palestinian sources reported 
that shots were directed at an IDF base in the Ramallah area and 
that a firebomb was thrown at a police outpost in the city. The 
policemen opened fire at the perpetrator, but he escaped. 
Searches were launched in the area. Another firebomb was 
thrown in Nabulus, but no casualties or damages were caused in 
this incident either. 
  Palestinian sources in Dayr al-Balah reported several 
incidents of stone-throwing at Border Police and settlers' cars. 
Stone- throwing incidents also occurred in the Qatif Bloc and 
the vicinity of Kfar Darom. 
  A military source noted yesterday that wanted men persist in 
their efforts to hide in the autonomous areas of Gaza and 
Jericho. The IDF has reinforced its patrols along the main roads 
in the Gaza Strip and the West Bank. 
  An evaluation report about the first month of activity of 
the 
joint Israeli-Palestinian patrols was issued yesterday. The 
report notes that no extraordinary events were registered during 
this period, except for a few shooting incidents. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

