<H3> <TI>   King Summons Parliament To Meet 29 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Summons Parliament To Meet 29 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1406154494 Hong Kong AFP in English 1530 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1406154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kathmandu, June 14 (AFP) -- King Birendra of Nepal 
has called for parliament to open its seventh session on June 29 
during which the future of Prime Minister Girija Prasad Koirala 
is likely to be decided. 
  In what observers said Tuesday is likely to be a stormy 
session, the ruling Nepali Congress (NC) will have to decide its 
differences, with the pro- and anti-Koirala camps still at 
loggerheads. 
  The prime minister is also expected to push for a change in 
party rules to allow him to hold two posts -- prime minister and 
party president -- which would give him control, they said. 
  Internal problems aside, the government also faces a renewed 
threat of public protests from the opposition Nepal Communist 
Party-ULited Marxist and Leninist. 
  Rebel NC MPs are also threatening to vote against an 
important financial bill unless Koirala resigns. 

</TEXT>

