<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting Between Hizballah, Israeli Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting Between Hizballah, Israeli Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1706095394 Paris AFP in English 0918 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1706095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tyre, Lebanon, June 17 (AFP) -- Clashes between 
Iranian-backed Hizballah guerrillas and allied Israeli 
militiamen killed a civilian woman and wounded four people in 
south Lebanon on Friday, police said. 
  The fighting broke out after Hizballah attacked an SLA 
outpost on the edge of Israel's self-declared "security zone" in 
south Lebanon with machine guns and B-7 rocket-propelled 
grenades, police in the southern port of Tyre said. 
  A group of guerrillas advanced close to the South Lebanese 
Army (SLA) outpost at al-Qantarah at mid-morning firing and as 
they pulled back the position came under a hail of mortar fire. 
  The SLA retaliated with a heavy artillery barrage on 
villages 
just north of the security zone, sending several shells crashing 
into civilian homes and killing a 50-year-old woman and wounding 
four other people, police added. 
  They fired more than 20 shells on the villages of Qabrikha, 
Tulin and Wadi al-Saluqi which face the al-Qantarah outpost and 
fires were reported in the region. 
  Two Israeli Cobra helicopters gunships also went into 
action, 
strafing a ravine used by the guerrillas to attack the security 
zone, police said. 
  On Thursday Israeli warplanes blasted a Hizballah base in 
the 
Iqlim al-Tuffah hills in south Lebanon. Two planes fired a 
missile at Mlita without causing any casualties. 
  Up to 45 guerrillas were killed on June 2 in an Israeli 
helicopter raid on a Hizballah training camp in the 
Syrian-controlled eastern Ba'labakk region. 
  Since then Israel has flown daily sorties over Lebanon 
searching to wipe out Hizballah resistance fighters. 

</TEXT>

