94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1606173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to new information on the attack on the 
Lebanese Consulate in Australia, unidentified persons threw 
gasoline and set fires around the consulate and at the entrance 
of the building. Australian firemen managed to extinguish the 
fire before it reached the inside of the building. Only the 
garage and the consul's car were damaged. 
  Diplomatic sources in Sidney said the consul had refused to 
sign forged documents which two fugitive suspects in the al-Zuq 
Church bombing and assassination of engineer Dany Sham'un, Tony 
'Ubayd and Jean Shahin tried to obtain. 
  The investigation links the fire to the indictment in 
connection with the two cases. 

</TEXT>

