<H3> <TI>   House Speaker Reiterates Government Stand on Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House Speaker Reiterates Government Stand on Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1606135094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1606135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] House of Representatives Speaker Brother Shaykh 
'Abdallah al-Ahmar has reiterated that the approach the 
political leadership, the government, and the legislative 
council in the Republic of Yemen adopt to settle the current 
crisis is that of the Yemeni people. This approach is embodied 
in the fact that Yemeni unity is the fate and lot of the people, 
and that this unity should not be harmed and is not subject to 
bargaining. He said the state welcomes and does not reject 
dialogue with any party, if this dialogue deals with Yemeni 
unity, the establishment of this unity, and with legitimacy, 
democracy, and political pluralism. Those who reject this are 
infidels. 
  This came at a news conference by the brother House of 
Representatives speaker today and attended by local, Arab, and 
foreign correspondents in Sanaa. 
  House of Representatives Speaker brother Shaykh 'Abdallah 
Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar emphasized that the Armed Forces, the forces 
of unity and legitimacy are confronting the forces of apostasy 
and secession, and that the Yemeni people from all walks of life 
support their Armed Forces. He explained that the forces of 
apostasy and secession have imposed war on our people, something 
our people do not want. He said the secessionists cannot have 
some of their illusions realized because Yemeni unity is a fact, 
the fruit of the struggle of the Yemeni people, their response 
to the Yemeni revolution's objectives, and the nucleus of 
comprehensive Arab unity. 

</TEXT>

