<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Abd-al-Rahman 'Ali al-Jifri, the deputy 
chairman of the Presidential Council, this morning inspected the 
air force and air defense headquarters, where he was briefed on 
the battle operations and the role of the pilots in implementing 
their responsibilities of defending the homeland and its 
achievements, and of foiling the plans of the enemy on the 
various fronts. The brother deputy chairman of the Presidential 
Council praised the pilots' efforts to protect democratic 
Yemen's airspace, and to prevent the enemy forces from achieving 
their military aims. 
  Brother 'Abd-al-Rahman al-Jifri also visited the families of 
victims of the barbarous indiscriminate shelling suffered by a 
number of residential districts in the capital, Aden, which came 
from the forces of the military regime in Sanaa and resulted in 
the deaths and wounding of 30 women, children, elderly persons, 
and peaceful civilians. Brother 'Abd-al-Rahman al-Jifri, the 
deputy chairman of the Presidential Council, expressed his 
sorrow and condolences at these horrible massacres perpetrated 
against the peaceful residents of the capital, Aden. The 
brother chairman of the Presidential Council then visited the 
naval command, saw for himself the fighting morale of the naval 
officers and enlisted men, and observed their intrepid role in 
supporting their brothers in the Armed Forces in repulsing and 
defeating the invading forces. 

</TEXT>

