<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 17 Jun (INA)--The Post, Telegraph, and 
Telephone Center in Sanaa has announced that telephone 
communications between Yemen and the world have resumed except 
those with the Gulf regimes and Egypt. 
  It is noteworthy that the telephone and telegraph lines 
inside Yemen were cut for several days after fighting broke out 
on 5 May. A week later, domestic communications resumed while 
Yemen's international telephone communications remained cut. 

