<F P=103> JN1706105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 17 Jun (INA)--The Yemeni security forces have 
arrested a saboteur whom the Saudi authorities sent to carry out 
acts of sabotage in Yemen as part of the Saudi conspiracy 
against Yemeni unity and the Saudi support for the secessionists 
in southern Yemen. 
  An informed Yemeni security source told an Iraqi News Agency 
correspondent in Sanaa today that the security forces last night 
arrested one of the Saudi regime's agents after he blew up a 
house in the area of Bajil, approximately 50 km east of the 
eastern al-Hudaydah Governorate. 
  The source explained that the explosion killed one citizen 
and wounded seven others. He also revealed that the security 
authorities arrested three other saboteurs who confessed they 
were recruited by the Saudi authorities to carry out bombings in 
Yemen. They were arrested after their recent arrival from Saudi 
Arabia, he added. 

