<H3> <TI>   Libyan Minister To `Oversee' Affairs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Libyan Minister To `Oversee' Affairs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606132894 Paris AFP in English 1255 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1606132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, June 16 (AFP) -- OPEC ministers failed to 
agree here Thursday [16 June] on the choice of a successor to 
OPEC Secretary General Subroto of Indonesia, delegates said. 
  Winding up a two-day meeting here, they agreed Libya's oil 
minister, 'Abdallah Salim al-Badri, should oversee the 
activities of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries 
secretariat until the next ministerial meeting in November, 
Saudi Arabia's oil minister Hisham Nazir said. 

</TEXT>

