<H3> <TI>   Guard Killed, Two Wounded in Asyut Shooting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guard Killed, Two Wounded in Asyut Shooting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1606175494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1620 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1606175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 16 Jun (MENA)--A guard was killed today and 
two others were wounded in Asyut when unidentified people opened 
fire at them at a checkpoint in Manfalut district. 
  A responsible security source in the Interior Ministry 
explained that at about 1100 today, unidentified people opened 
fire at guardsmen Rayyan Ahmad Muhammad, Salihin 'Abd-al-Hamid 
Jum'ah, and 'Abd-al-Nazir 'Abd-al-Hamid Hasanayn, who work at 
the Umm al-Qusur police station in Manfalut district. 
  The source said that the first guardsman was killed in the 
incident and the two others were wounded and taken to the 
hospital in Manfalut for treatment. 
  Commanders of the Asyut security directorate, criminal 
investigation personnel, and criminal laboratory experts went to 
the scene of the incident, and the prosecution was informed to 
begin an investigation. 

</TEXT>

