<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel Releases Another 80 Prisoners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel Releases Another 80 Prisoners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1706095794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 17 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1706095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Another 80 Palestinian prisoners who are members of 
the rejectionist organizations were released from prison today 
and sent to their homes in the territories. Our correspondent 
Moti Amir reports that these prisoners agreed to sign a 
declaration vowing not to act against the peace agreement. 
Another 570 prisoners who were scheduled to be released in 
accordance with the Cairo agreement refused to sign the 
declaration. 
  Sa'ib 'Urayqat accused Israel of violating the Cairo 
agreement with regard to the Palestinian prisoners. In a news 
conference in Jericho, 'Urayqat said that according to the 
agreement all the political prisoners, as he put it, must be 
released unconditionally. He noted that Israel's demand that the 
prisoners sign any document constitutes blackmail. In his 
opinion, the fact that the prisoners are taken to Jericho also 
represents a violation of the agreement because Israel must 
allow them to return to their homes. 
  'Urayqat also criticized the roadblocks erected by Israel on 
the highways leading to the autonomous area, saying they prevent 
tourists from entering the self-rule areas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

