<H3> <TI>   Hamas Deputy Leader Released by Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Deputy Leader Released by Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1606171494 Paris AFP in English 1509 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1606171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gaza City, Gaza Strip, June 16 (AFP) -- Israel 
released the deputy leader of the Islamic Resistance Movement 
HAMAS on Thursday among several hundred Palestinians set free, 
Palestinian sources said. 
  Sa'id Abu-Musamih, 47, one of the co-founders of the Moslem 
fundamentalist group, was serving life for his activities. 
  When Israel arrested HAMAS chief Shaykh Ahmad Yasin in 1989, 
Abu-Musamih took over as head of the movement before he was 
imprisoned the following year. 
  Yasin, sentenced to life in 1991 for murder and incitement 
to 
violence, remains in jail having refused an offer of freedom 
conditional on a pledge to renounce terrorism. 

</TEXT>

