<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Dismisses Signers of Unauthorized Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Dismisses Signers of Unauthorized Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1606155094 London AL-QUDS AL-'ARABI in Arabic 15 Jun 94 p 
11 </F>

<F P=103> PM1606155094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-QUDS AL-'ARABI </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sami 'Abudi and Samiyah Nakhkhul: "PLO Dismisses </F>
Officials Who Exceeded Their Authority"] 
  [Excerpt] Jerusalem, Cairo -- A Palestinian official said 
Tuesday that the PLO has dismissed officials who signed an 
interim agreement with Israel confining the movement of 
Palestinian prisoners released by Israel to the autonomy area of 
Jericho. He added that these officials, who were members of the 
[Joint] Liaison Committee with Israel which observes security in 
the autonomy areas of Jericho and the Gaza Strip, were not 
authorized to sign. After seven tense hours, 287 prisoners were 
handed over to the Palestinian police in Jericho last week. 
Israel says that the Cairo agreement on autonomy allows it to 
insist that the prisoners handed over to the Palestinians should 
remain in the autonomy areas. Faysal al-Husayni, the most 
senior PLO official in the West Bank, has stated that the person 
who signed the agreement had no authority to sign, and that is 
why a decision was issued to replace the Palestinian Security 
Committee with another committee. 
  Al-Husayni left for Jordan yesterday, Tuesday, and is 
expected to travel to Tunis for a meeting with 'Arafat. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-37158 </DOCNO>
