<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authority Member on Resignation `Threat' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authority Member on Resignation `Threat' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1606145594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1000 GMT 16 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1606145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with Dr. 'Azmi al-Shu'aybi, member of </F>
the Palestinian National Authority, by Sa'id Mu'addi; place and 
date not given; from the "With the Midday Events" program -- 
recorded] 
  [Text] [Mu'addi] Dr. 'Azmi al-Shu'aybi: You and your FIDA 
[Palestinian Democratic Federation Party] colleague, Yasir 
'Abd-Rabbuh, are threatening to resign from the Palestinian 
National Authority [PNA]. Why? 
  [Al-Shu'aybi] It is not a threat, but an expression of our 
party's stand on the preparations under way by the PNA. We have 
serious observations about the PNA's procrastination in the 
adoption of sufficient and necessary measures to seriously and 
directly assume its role, so that an authority vacuum does not 
occur in the territories from which the Israeli authority has 
withdrawn. 
  [Mu'addi] What are these reservations, doctor? 
  [Al-Shu'aybi] First, brother Yasir 'Arafat and the essential 
PLO leading cadre should quickly return to the territories. 
This particularly applies to the group that followed up the 
negotiations with Israel on the Cairo agreement. Now that 
brothers Nabil Sha'th and 'Abd-al-Razzaq al-Yahya have returned, 
it is necessary that other brothers who took part in the 
formulation on this agreement return so they can directly 
supervise its immediate implementation. Administrative and 
financial issues should be completed so this authority can 
assume its role. So far, we still feel there is procrastination 
and that the question is not taken seriously. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. 'Azmi, is this stand by you perhaps because of 
the marginalization of the FIDA status in the PNA? 
  [Al-Shu'aybi] This is irrelevant, for FIDA has willingly 
selected its two portfolios. Brother Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh has 
selected the culture and arts portfolio. I selected the youth 
care and sports portfolios. In fact, all those involved have 
selected their portfolios with complete freedom. So far, we 
cannot say that serious work has started in either of these two 
fields, or any other field. When we have made some observations 
public, they were intended to be addressed to all fields of 
Palestinian authority rather than those two fields only. I 
believe the vacuum resulting from the PNA's failure so far to 
assume its role seriously damages more than only FIDA and its 
representatives on the PNA. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. 'Azmi, a last question: Have contacts been 
held with the PLO leadership, particularly Yasir 'Arafat in this 
regard? 
  [Al-Shu'aybi] The FIDA representatives in Tunis are 
authorized to raise this issue with brother Yasir 'Arafat. I 
believe a special session was held in Tunis yesterday to discuss 
these issues, including the FIDA observations about the 
preparations so far. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. 'Azmi al-Shu'aybi, member of the PNA, thank 
you 
very much. 
  [Al-Shu'aybi] Not at all. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

