<H3> <TI>   Nineteen Reportedly Killed in Kashmir Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nineteen Reportedly Killed in Kashmir Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1606153894 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1606153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In occupied Kashmir, 14 Indian soldiers have been 
killed in clashes with mojahedin. Six Indian soldiers were 
killed when mojahedin attacked a military convoy in Rafiabad 
area; seven others were shot dead in a clash with mojahedin in 
Kishtwar. Mojahedin also suffered five casualties. 
  Reports say a three-day strike is being observed in the held 
valley to protest the killing of the Jihad Force chief 
commander, Nazir Ahmad Shah, by Indian soldiers. Thousands of 
people raising anti-India slogans took part in the funeral of 
the martyred mojahed in Bandipura. A big protest demonstration 
was also reported from Kishtwar where a mosque was desecrated by 
Indian forces. 

</TEXT>

