  [Text] In Kashmir Valley, six persons, including four 
militants, were killed in the last 24 hours. An official 
spokesman said in Srinagar today that the security forces 
arrested 39 militants, including five hard-core, and recovered a 
large quantity of arms and ammunition. Meanwhile, the day 
curfew was lifted in Bhadarwah town of Doda District today 
following improvement in the situation. Night curfew from 1900 
till 0700 will however continue as a precautionary measure. 

</TEXT>

