<H3> <TI>   African Leaders Arrive for Regional Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    African Leaders Arrive for Regional Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Niger President Makes Statement </H4>

<F P=102> LD1506194394 Tripoli JANA in Arabic 1830 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli JANA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Tripoli, 15 Jun (JANA) -- Niger President 
Mahamane Ousmane and his accompanying delegation arrived in 
Tripoli today for a visit to the great Jamahiriyah. An official 
welcoming ceremony was accorded to the president of Niger. 
Colonel 'Abu Bakr Jabir Yunis led the welcoming delegation. 
[passage omitted] 
  President Ousmane made a statement to the Jamahiriyah News 
Agency (JANA) in which he expressed happiness for his visit to 
the great Jamahiriyah. Ousmane affirmed that his visit falls 
within the framework of bolstering relations and cooperation in 
all areas between the two countries. 
  President Ousmane reiterated his country's support for the 
great Jamahiriyah in the face of the unjust sanctions, imposed 
through the so-called the Security Council. He noted that the 
Libyan people are a fraternal people. Ousmane said Niger is 
affected by anything that harms Libya. He called for the 
lifting of the unjust sanctions. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

