  [Excerpts] Tyrant Saddam's authorities have declared a 
state of emergency in the (?west) of al-Nasiriyah Governorate in 
southern Iraq following an attack by one the Islamic resistance 
forces mujahidin on the command headquarters of [words 
indistinct] on 3 June. Scores of officers and men of the 
tyrant's forces were killed and wounded and [words indistinct]. 
  Reporting this from southern Iraq, our sources said the 
authorities intensified the presence of their forces in 
al-Nasiriyah and nearby cities and villages in the marshlands in 
