<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy Briefs Arab League Chief on Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Envoy Briefs Arab League Chief on Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2006092994 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0900 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2006092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 
'Abd-al-Majid today met with Lakhdar Ibrahimi, the UN envoy who 
is trying to find a solution to the Yemeni crisis. They 
reviewed the latest developments in the crisis and the efforts 
being made to implement a cease-fire. The UN envoy briefed the 
Arab League secretary general on the results of his talks with 
the Yemeni parties and the Arab leaders he met during his visit. 
Ibrahimi also briefed him on the results of the talks with the 
North and South Yemeni delegations in Cairo last night to end 
the crisis. 
  An Arab League source stated that the meeting took place 
within the framework of the continuing coordination and 
cooperation between the Arab League and the United Nations on 
the Yemeni crisis. 

</TEXT>

