<H3> <TI>   ICO To Hold Ministerial Council Meeting in Tunis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ICO To Hold Ministerial Council Meeting in Tunis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706171994 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 1620 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 17 Jun (SPA) -- Hamid al-Ghabid, secretary 
general of the Organization of the Islamic Conference [ICO], 
today said that the meeting of the Organization's Ministerial 
Council would be held next September or December in Tunis. 
  In a newspaper interview published in Tunis, he said that 
consultations are under way between the Organization and Tunisia 
to determine the time of the meeting. 
  He pointed out that the meeting would concentrate on 
discussing the situation of the city of Jerusalem within the 
framework of the peace process, which the ICO supports, in 
addition to the situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

