<H3> <TI>   Sha'th: 'Arafat in Jericho by End of Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th: 'Arafat in Jericho by End of Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1906181794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic GMT 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1906181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, minister of planning and 
international cooperation in the Palestinian National Authority, 
said today that Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat will visit 
Jericho at the end of June. 
  Sha'th also announced that the Palestinian-Israeli peace 
negotiations will resume in one week to settle all the issues 
left unresolved by the Gaza-Jericho Agreement. Sha'th added 
that he agreed with Amnon Shahaq, head of the Israeli delegation 
to the Palestinian-Israeli Liaison Committee, on convening the 
committee on 27 June to discuss the hand over of the rest of the 
West Bank to Palestinian self-rule earlier than planned. 

</TEXT>

