PNA also reportedly intends to visit the al-Aqsa Mosque on the 
Temple Mount and churches in the Old City during his visit to 
Jerusalem. [passage omitted] [end recording] 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 0500 GMT on 19 June 
adds: "Tzomet has called on the prime minister not to allow 
Nabil Sha'th to hold a meeting with the Palestine Authority 
members in Orient House in Jerusalem. Knesset Member Moshe 
Peled told our correspondent Hayim Hecht that the ability to 
prevent this meeting will be the government's first test of the 
seriousness of its declarations concerning Jerusalem."] 

