<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th: Meeting Only `Reception' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th: Meeting Only `Reception' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1906101794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 19 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1906101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nabil Sha'th has explained that his meeting with 
members of the Palestinian Authority [PA] scheduled for tomorrow 
at Orient House in East Jerusalem will be a reception and not a 
working session or an official meeting. He told our 
correspondent Moti Amir that he will confer with the PA members 
in Jericho this afternoon to brief them about his meeting with 
Major General Amnon Shahaq, during which he will discuss the 
continuation of the negotiations on the implementation of the 
autonomy agreements. Dr. Sha'th said that a reception, and not 
an official meeting, will be held for him at Orient House. He 
added that he will pray at al-Aqsa Mosque and visit churches in 
East Jerusalem tomorrow. 
  Jerusalem Mayor Ehud Olmert has called on the prime minister 
to take immediate action to thwart Sha'th's plans to visit 
Jerusalem. He told our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky that such a 
visit would constitute a violation of the autonomy agreements. 
  The National Religious Party [NRP] and Moledet have joined 
the call to prevent the PA from holding a meeting in East 
Jerusalem. Our correspondent Hayim Hecht quotes NRP leader 
Zvulun Hammer as saying: Giving the PA a foothold in Jerusalem 
is tantamount to letting it trample on the State of Israel's 
honor. Moledet leader Rehav'am Ze'evi said the Palestinians are 
making a mockery of the State of Israel, and that is why Rabin 
must prevent the meeting in Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

