<H3> <TI>   Fatah Official on Settlers' Bid To `Assassinate' Him </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Official on Settlers' Bid To `Assassinate' Him </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1806201194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 18 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1806201194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Several shots were fired this evening at the car of 
Sami Abu-Samahdanah, one of the Fatah leaders in the Gaza Strip. 
The bullets struck the vehicle, but Abu-Samahdanah was unharmed. 
  Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that Abu-Samahdanah 
lodged a complaint with the Palestinian-Israeli coordinating 
committee. He asserted that the shots had been fired from 
inside the Jewish settlement of Netzarim, in an attempt to 
assassinate him. 

</TEXT>

