<H3> <TI>   Israel Said Denying Entry to Labor Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel Said Denying Entry to Labor Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2006090694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 20 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2006090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israel has so far prevented Dr. Samir Ghawshah, the 
official in charge of the labor portfolio in the Palestinian 
Authority; Fatah Central Committee member Abu-Mahir Ghunaym; and 
poet Mahmud Darwish from entering the autonomy area. Our 
correspondent Moti Amir has learned this from Palestinian 
sources. Fadil Tahbub, member of the Popular Struggle Front, 
told our correspondent that Dr. Ghawshah, leader of the front, 
seeks to enter the autonomy area in order to turn his 
organization into a political party which will be able to run in 
the autonomy elections. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 0800 GMT on 20 June 
adds: "A senior security source told our correspondent Moti Amir 
that nobody is preventing Samir Ghawshah from entering the 
autonomy area. The source denied the Palestinian sources' claims 
that Israel is preventing Dr. Ghawshah from entering the 
autonomy." 
  ["Dr. Ghawshah told our correspondent that the PLO has 
submitted a list of names of approximately 500 PLO members who 
are slated to arrive in the autonomy, including approximately 
one-third of the Fatah Central Committee members in Tunis. So 
far, Israel has not agreed to their request to enter the 
autonomy."] 

</TEXT>

