<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Official Denies Torture Accusations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Official Denies Torture Accusations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1706144494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 17 Jun 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM1706144494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Palestinian Official Denies </F>
Accusations of Torturing Detainees in Strip's Prisons"] 
  [Excerpt] London, Tunis, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- A senior 
Palestinian police official in the Gaza Strip has denied that 
detainees are tortured. The official said that these are 
unreliable allegations which have nothing to do with reality. 
The official was answering a question about statements made by 
Mu'tazz Hakim, whom the police arrested on 6 June at his 
residence in al-Nasr district -- Block 60, Gaza City. 
  The official said that this person was not subjected to 
torture or any other violations. Proof of this is that the 
human rights association visited him during his detention. 
  But Kahil, who joined the police service recently to work in 
the criminal investigation section in al-Rimal station, spoke 
about the circumstances of his arrest and the torture he was 
subjected to during four days of detention. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

