<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PFLP, DFLP Debating `National Salvation' Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PFLP, DFLP Debating `National Salvation' Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1906111994 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 19 Jun 94 pp 24, 
20 </F>

<F P=103> JN1906111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Riyad Mansur in Amman] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine [PFLP] and the Democratic Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine [DFLP] have called for electing a new political 
leadership for the Palestinian people, rebuilding the Unified 
National Leadership of the Intifadah on new foundations, as well 
as holding an Islamic-Christian conference to defend the Arabism 
of Jerusalem. 
  This is part of a draft plan for national salvation which is 
being debated by the cadres of the two fronts as a prelude to 
endorsing it within the framework of their unionist plan. This 
constitutes a step along the road of unity between the 
Palestinian left and its democratic and revolutionary forces. 
The program asserts that the two fronts are willing to set up 
an alliance under this program with all forces in the 
Palestinian arena. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

