<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visit by Presidents of Mali, Niger, Burkina Faso </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit by Presidents of Mali, Niger, Burkina Faso </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Malian President Gives Banquet Speech </H4>

<F P=102> LD1706154594 Tripoli Voice of Greater Arab Homeland in 
Arabic 1223 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Voice of Greater Arab Homeland </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Speech given by Malian President Alpha Omar Konare at </F>
banquet given by Libyan leader Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi in Tripoli 
on 16 June--recorded] 
  [Excerpt] Dear brothers and friends. The presence of 
Blaise Compaore, Mahamane Ousmane, and I around our brother host 
Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi this evening is not a mere coincidence. 
It is in the name of common history and our preoccupations now 
and in the future, a future we want to build together. We all 
reject the current misfortune of our continent. We all refuse 
to believe that our continent is a continent of hatred and 
violence. What is happening in Rwanda and elsewhere does not 
reflect the reality of our continent. This misery and hatred 
are not a fatality, and we have the means to end them. Our 
presence here also expresses this loud and clear. 
  Dear friend al-Qadhdhafi, we have come here to express our 
solidarity to you and to your people. [applause] The journey 
here will never be too long or too uncomfortable. What we are 
doing this evening has already been done by the 53 African 
states in Tunis. This was already done by the Nonaligned 
Movement, by the Arab League, and by the Islamic Conference last 
year and this year. We hope that our voice will be heard. We 
will do everything so the message gets through in every scene 
tomorrow. We have the obligation to do so. The future of the 
Libyan people concerns us. It is important that conditions be 
created today to continue the march. 
  It is important that justice should be done today. We stand 
by your side in this struggle, dear brother. You are aware of 
our problems and the difficulties we are going through at the 
moment. We will have to do everything in our power to prevent 
our countries from sliding toward ethnic, racial, regional, and 
religious conflicts. We cannot fight the battle for democracy 
and nationalism on ethnic, racial, regional, and religious 
basis. Our continent needs social justice and solidarity today. 
It is with solidarity, hard work, and commitment that we will 
be able to face this challenge. We need solidarity, and we 
should move rapidly towards strong integration of our countries. 
Regional integration should not be an empty word or a mere 
slogan, otherwise, we condemn our continent to bankruptcy by the 
end of the century. Regional integration is a must. We believe 
in it, and we will work for it. If we fail to do so, we and our 
children will be doomed. [passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-37225 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes118_d_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
