<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   FRY Envoy Thanks al-Qadhdhafi for `Objective' Role </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRY Envoy Thanks al-Qadhdhafi for `Objective' Role </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906194694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1838 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1906194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tripoli, 19 Jun (TANJUG): Libyan leader Mu'ammar 
al-Qadhdhafi today received Dusan Simeonovic, Yugoslav 
ambassador to Tripoli, who handed him a message by Zoran Lilic, 
the president of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia. The 
ambassador passed on the high regard of the Yugoslav leadership 
and the FRY Government for the objective and constructive 
position the head of the Libyan state has had since the 
beginning of the Yugoslav crisis and Libya's for consistently 
friendly relations with Yugoslavia. 
  Thanking him for the message, Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi 
reiterated his position of respect and support for the efforts 
the FRY Government is making toward a peaceful and just 
resolution of the conflict in the former Yugoslavia. 
  They laid particular stress on the usefulness of the ongoing 
high-level dialogue between the two countries and the interest 
both sides are showing in its resumption. 

</TEXT>

