<H3> <TI>   Opposition Front To Convene National Council </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Front To Convene National Council </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1706155094 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 17 Jun 94 p4 </F>
<F P=103> PM1706155094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Libyan Salvation Front Completes </F>
Preparations for National Council"] 
  [Text] London, AL-HAYAH -- Ibrahim Sahd, official 
spokesman of the National Front for the Salvation of Libya 
[NFSL] (opposition), has stated that "the NFSL's organizational 
situation is excellent" and that preparations "have been 
completed for convening the NFSL National Council in the near 
future. It will be a major demonstration for the Libyan 
oppositionists to confirm their options and define the new 
courses of action." 
  He told AL-HAYAH yesterday that 35 representatives of the 
Central American region met some days ago and elected 10 people 
to represent them in the National Council along with five 
observers, and that representataves of Western America had met 
earlier and elected eight representatives and four observers. 
He added that this process was carried out in most NFSL offices 
and branches around the world. 

</TEXT>

