<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP Official: Delegation Arrives fo Cairo Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Official: Delegation Arrives fo Cairo Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1806205694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2045 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1806205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 18 Jun (MENA) -- Mr. Salim Salih Muhammad, 
member of the Presidential Council in the recently declared 
Republic of Yemen in Aden and assistant secretary of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party [YSP], has stated that talks will take place 
tomorrow, Sunday 19 June, in Cairo to discuss a cease-fire in 
Yemen. 
  He said that a ranking Yemeni delegation has arrived in 
Cairo 
to discuss the mechanism for a cease-fire. The delegation will 
meet with Egyptian officials to inform them of the latest 
developments in the situation in Yemen and the effects of the 
war so far. 
  He added that the major objective now is to stop the 
bloodshed among the sons of Yemen in order to preserve the 
remaining institutions of the country. 

</TEXT>

