<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northern Delegation To Join Cease-Fire Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Delegation To Join Cease-Fire Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1906080294 Paris AFP in English 0735 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1906080294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, June 19 (AFP) -- A northern Yemeni delegation 
will leave here Sunday [19 June] for Cairo to attend ceasefire 
talks sponsored by the United Nations, an official here said. 
  Sanaa told UN special envoy Lakhdar Ibrahimi that it would 
send a delegation to Cairo "on condition the (meeting) is held 
in the context of the Republic of Yemen and not that of two 
states as the southerners want," he told AFP. 
  The meeting will last one day, said the official who 
requested anonymity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

