<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Basindwah Comments on Joint Military Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Basindwah Comments on Joint Military Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1806054194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1806054194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Yemeni News Agency, SABA', has asked Foreign 
Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah about reports disseminated by 
news agencies that the Government of the Republic of Yemen has 
agreed on the participation of Arab and foreign countries in the 
committee that will be in charge of consolidating a cease-fire. 
Brother Muhammad Salim Basindwah said: It should be clear that 
we have informed brother Lakhdar Ibrahimi, the personal envoy of 
the UN secretary general, and a number of Arab leaders that the 
Government of the Republic of Yemen agrees on activating the 
joint military committee, which includes Yemeni military 
officials and representatives from Jordan and the Sultanate 
Oman. He added that the Yemeni Government agreed on adding 
representatives from Syria and the Kingdom of Morocco, for the 
Arab side, in addition to the U.S. and French military attaches 
from the non-Arab side. 

</TEXT>

