<H3> <TI>   Government To `Retaliate' If `Separatists' Recognized </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To `Retaliate' If `Separatists' Recognized </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1706122094 Baghdad INA in English 1150 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1706122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, June 17, INA -- Yemeni Planning Minister 
'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani warned against recognizing the 
separatists in the southern provinces. 
  In press statements published by Yemeni press here today, 
Mr. 
al-Iryani said his government would retaliate against such 
recognition including the severing of diplomatic relations with 
any country recognizing the separatists. 

</TEXT>

