<H3> <TI>   Al-Jifri Appeals to UN To Stop Sanaa Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Jifri Appeals to UN To Stop Sanaa Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1806204194 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1900 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1806204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1900 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by 'Abd-al-Rahman 'Ali al-Jifri, "vice </F>
chairman of the Presidential Council"; place and date not given] 
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] The refusal by the Sanaa regime 
to accept all the resolutions and appeals of the world has been 
accompanied by moves on the battlefronts to launch successive 
attacks on our brave forces who are defending Aden, its vital 
installations, and the civilians from among the sons of our 
people in a foolish and amazing insistence they [Sanaa regime] 
continue to attempt impossible advances aiming to occupy the 
steadfast city. 
  As I announce this to the world I would like to stress that 
the government of the Democratic Republic of Yemen has been 
asking for the necessity of convening an urgent meeting of the 
UN Security Council so that steps may be taken to put an end to 
the Sanaa regime's defiance of the resolutions of the Security 
Council and the appeals of the international community. 
  I also appeal to the fraternal Arab and Muslim countries and 
the friendly countries, as well as the five permanent members of 
the Security Council, to take decisive measures with regard to 
the Sanaa regime which is rejecting everything and insisting on 
the logic of force, particularly after this has been 
demonstrated to everyone. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

