<H3> <TI>   Asnaj Makes Appeal to UN Secretary General </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Asnaj Makes Appeal to UN Secretary General </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1706190094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1706190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Republic of Yemen has informed the 
UN secretary general, Dr. Butrus-Ghali, of the latest 
developments in the situation in our country, and the dangers of 
the escalation resorted to by the Sanaa ruling regime 
represented in striking the cities and the residential quarters, 
especially Aden. 
  The Democratic Republic of Yemen appealed to Dr. 
Butrus-Ghali 
to submit these developments to the security council. This was 
stated by 'Abdallah 'Abd-al-Majid al-Asnaj, deputy prime 
minister and minister of foreign affairs. He said that the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen also demanded the UN Security 
Council to treat 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his regime as war 
criminals, confirming that our country was moving at the 
political and diplomatic levels to stop the war. 

</TEXT>

