<F P=103> EA1906174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1620 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have just received this news report. A 
responsible source at the Ministry of Defense of the Democratic 
Republic of Yemen has categorically denied the report carried by 
the news media of the ruling military regime in Sanaa this 
evening that our military aircraft raided the city of 
al-Hudaydah and bombed the electricity-generating station at 
Mocha. The source confirmed that this report has absolutely no 
truth and is part of the cheap misleading information for which 
the stooges of the ruling military regime in Sanaa and their 
other news media have become famous for. This is known to 
everyone in the two parts of Yemen and, indeed, in the Arab 
homeland and the entire world. 
  The responsible source warned that this media report carried 
by the Sanaa media could be a new pretext to continue the 
shelling of the economic installations as well as the peaceful 
residential quarters in the Aden Governorate. The ruling 
military regime has grown accustomed to this recently after 
failing to achieve the strategic and military objectives of the 
war. This is a matter on which we cannot remain silent and it 
will be confronted with force. 

</TEXT>

