<H3> <TI>   Aden Reports North Firing Katyusha Rockets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Reports North Firing Katyusha Rockets </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806095894 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 0811 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 18 Jun (KUNA) -- Seventeen people have been 
wounded in fierce fighting at the fronts surrounding Aden. The 
fighting continued until the early hours of 18 June. 
  The northern forces managed last night -- for the second 
consecutive day -- to advance a personnel carrier mounted with 
Katyusha rockets in order to shell the port of Aden; however, 
the rockets fell on some residential areas close to the port. 
Other rockets fell on the area surrounding Aden airport, 
injuring 17 people. 
  Last Thursday, a northern Katyusha vehicle managed to 
penetrate southern defense lines in the Bi'r Ahmad area, some 30 
km northwest of Aden, where it fired its rockets and hit a 
shipyard in the port area. Another vehicle managed at dawn 
yesterday to penetrate several kilometers inside the Sabr front, 
situated 30 km north of Aden, and fired its rockets, which hit a 
military camp near the area of Aden airport. 

</TEXT>

