<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali has ordered an 
increase in the number of Tunisian troops to the UN forces in 
Rwanda. This took place when the president received Defense 
Minister Abdelaziz Ben Dhia this morning in Carthage Palace. 
This decision gives substance to the determination of our 
country shown during the OAU [Organization of African Unity] 
summit in Tunis of assuming its responsibility in settling 
conflicts in Africa. President Ben Ali, the current chairman of 
the OAU, stressed that this initiative is a response to the need 
shown in the African summit for an effective contribution by 
African countries to the settlement of hot conflicts in the 
continent, within the framework of cooperation between the OAU 
and the United Nations. [passage omitted] 

