exchange of visits between the various bodies concerned with 
this cooperation. It was decided that the Tunisian side would 
move this cooperation forward by contributing its expertise in 
carrying out development programs in Namibia. 
  On the other hand, the official spokesman said that the 
talks 
dealt with the situation in the Arab Maghreb and Southwest 
Africa as well as the challenges facing the OAU. [passage 
omitted] 

