<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Opposes Sanctions Against DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Opposes Sanctions Against DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1706152194 Delhi ISI Diplomatic Information Service in 
English 1447 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1706152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi ISI Diplomatic Information Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by official spokesman; date not given] </F>
  [TEXT] 1. We have been closely following the developments 
in the Korean Peninsula. We trust that all the parties 
concerned will exercise the maximum restraint so that peace and 
tranquility can be maintained in the region, and existing 
tensions can be eliminated. 
  2. We follow with great interest the current mission being 
undertaken by former president, Jimmy Carter of the U.S. and 
hope that the positive first steps which have been achieved can 
be further built upon. 
  3. India abstained on the resolution adopted by the board of 
governors of the IAEA [International Atomic Energy Agency] last 
week, our view being that punitive measures adopted in the 
United Nations or elsewhere could exacerbate matters at this 
stage, making a resolution of the issue more difficult. We hope 
that negotiations will continue through which a way will be 
found to peacefully resolve this crisis. 

</TEXT>

