<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Having received the blessing of senior government 
elements, Knesset House Committee Chairman Yehoshu'a Matza has 
submitted a bill prohibiting the existence of Palestinian 
institutions and societies in East Jerusalem in violation of the 
relevant basic law. The new bill says that Palestinian 
institutions inherently reject the existence of the State of 
Israel. 
  Knesset Member Matza told our correspondent Hayim Hecht that 
the officials with whom he coordinated his bill were frustrated 
by the fact that a similar bill initiated by the prime minister 
had fallen through. 

