<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Planes Attack Iqlim al-Tuffah Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1906092094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0900 GMT 19 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1906092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israeli warplanes attacked the Iqlim al-Tuffah 
region in the south at 1125 today, targeting Mlita and 
al-Luwayzah with two successive raids. Israeli warplanes 
continue to fly over the area. 
  Israeli warplanes fired four air-to-surface missiles on 
Mlita 
Hill at 1110. The Lebanese Army opened fire on the planes. The 
Israeli air raids were accompanied and preceded by intensive air 
activity over al-Nabatiyah and Iqlim al-Tuffah. 
  At 1105 the warplanes fired two rockets on Jabal Safi in 
Iqlim al-Tuffah. 
  The air raids have caused an atmosphere of fear and panic 
among the citizens, who have remained in their homes. There are 
no reports of casualties yet. Only material damage has been 
done. 

</TEXT>

