<H3> <TI>   Army Issues Directorate on Deployment Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Issues Directorate on Deployment Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1806085294 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0800 GMT 18 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1806085294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lebanese Army units continue to be deployed in 
specific areas in [Jabal Lubnan]. Military sources told the 
NATIONAL NEWS AGENCY that the deployment process will continue 
for three days. They said that approximately 8,000 officers and 
personnel from the 3d, 6th, 10th, and 11th brigades and the 3d 
intervention regiment have been deployed in several villages 
beginning from Qabb Ilyas. 
  The Lebanese Army Guidance Directorate issued the following 
statement: 
  Within the framework of implementing the council of 
ministers' resolutions relating to consolidating security, 
extending the state authority, and returning displaced people to 
their homes and villages, at dawn today the Lebanese Army began 
the final deployment operations in Jabal Lubnan from the 
al-Awwali river in the south and the Upper al-Matn area in the 
north. The objectives and tasks of this operation are to create 
a suitable and permanently secure atmosphere and a return to a 
normal life for the return of the displaced people to their 
homes, and to strengthen national coexistence, which is one of 
the main components of accord. 
  On this occasion, the army command calls on the citizens, 
both returnees and residents, to contribute to this historic 
event, bring about family reunions, renounce past grudges, and 
aspire to a prosperous future for themselves and their sons 
under the umbrella of security, law, and justice. 

</TEXT>

