<H3> <TI>   Junblatt on Media Reportage of Army Deployment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Junblatt on Media Reportage of Army Deployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1906122794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 19 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1906122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Housing Affairs Minister Walid Junblatt by </F>
unidentified correspondent on 19 June; place not given -- 
recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [Junblatt] I have already explained that the Army 
has been present in the mountains. In agreement and 
coordination with Army Commander General Emile Lahhud, the Army 
has been reinforced. However, the Lebanese media have described 
the matter as if the Army has entered a forbidden area. This is 
wrong. The Army and the internal security forces have been 
there. The refugees began to return last year. They will 
continue to return where they can with the help of the ministry 
and the Army. 
  [Correspondent] Do you consider what happened yesterday and 
today a reinforcement of the Army's presence? 
  [Junblatt] This is a new security plan. I have personally 
asked for some action to give assurances [to the returnees]. 
There are steps that have been taken by the Army for reasons 
only known to it. We do not deal in the Army's military 
affairs. However, the Army has been there. What is the reason 
for all this drum beating and trumpeting as if the Army has 
entered the Israeli- occupied south? [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

