<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cairo Hosts Talks on Yemen Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cairo Hosts Talks on Yemen Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Northern Yemeni Delegation Arrives </H4>

<F P=102> NC1906153094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1504 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1906153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 Jun (MENA)--A Yemeni delegation led by 
'Ali Mansur Rashid, member of the standing committee of the 
General People's Congress, arrived in Cairo from Sanaa this 
afternoon. In his arrival statement, the Yemeni official said 
that this visit is within the framework of efforts to implement 
Security Council Resolution 924. He said: We are happy to 
visit Cairo, which is the haven of all Arabs. He noted that he 
is carrying a message from the Yemeni Government to Lakhdar 
Brahimi, envoy of the UN secretary general to Yemen, who is 
currently in Cairo. Rashid pointed out that the situation is 
creating optimism and that they have come as representatives of 
two sides of the coalition parties in the Republic of Yemen, in 
addition to the Yemeni Socialist Party. [as received] 
  Rashid said that the delegations will discuss reviving and 
forming a military committee to monitor the cease-fire, noting 
that the delay in forming the committee is due to the south's 
intransigence. Concerning the possibility of requesting Arab 
forces to help monitor the cease-fire, he said that the 
situation has not yet reached that point and that it is still 
confined to the framework of the Yemeni state. He added that it 
has not ruled out the possibility of the parties' seeking the 
help of Arab forces. 

</TEXT>

