BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 Jun (MENA)--'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani, 
member of the Yemeni Presidential Council, arrived in Cairo this 
evening on a visit to Egypt. 
  In an arrival statement, the Yemeni official expressed his 
pleasure at visiting Cairo, adding that he is carrying a message 
for President Husni Mubarak from Lieutenant General 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Yemeni Presidential Council. 
The message deals with the current situation in Yemen and 
relations between the two fraternal countries. 
  The Yemeni official was received upon arrival by Information 
Minister Safwat al-Sharif, Assistant Foreign Minister Badr 
Hammam, and members of the Yemeni Embassy in Cairo. 

