<H4>    South Sees `No Positive Results' </H4>

<F P=102> NC2006060994 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0400 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2006060994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] 'Abdallah al-Asnaj, appointed foreign minister of 
the self-declared Democratic Republic of Yemen, has stated that 
the South Yemen delegation will leave Cairo today to resume its 
tour of the Arab Maghreb states after it became apparent that 
Lakhdar Brahimi's meeting with the Sanaa delegation produced no 
positive results. Al-Asnaj praised President Husni Mubarak's 
efforts to end the tragic war in Yemen. 

