<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Returns From OAU Summit, Geneva </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Returns From OAU Summit, Geneva </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1706160294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1706160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Husni Mubarak, Mrs. Mubarak, and the 
delegation that accompanied the president during his visit to 
Tunis to attend the OAU summit and to Geneva to receive the UN 
population award for 1994 returned safely to the homeland this 
afternoon. 
  President Mubarak has decided to donate the money award he 
received from the UN to the Ministry of Local Government. The 
money will be used to set up a number of family planning centers 
in the Upper Egyptian villages. 

</TEXT>

