<H3> <TI>   League Appeals to Yemeni Leaders To Stop Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Appeals to Yemeni Leaders To Stop Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1606181894 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1606181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Arab League has again appealed to the Yemeni 
leaders to stop the fighting immediately in implementation of UN 
Security Council Resolution 924 and in response to Arab and 
international efforts. It has called on them to begin 
negotiations immediately to safeguard the remaining resources of 
the fraternal Yemeni people. 
  An Arab League official has said that Arab League Secretary 
General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid is continuing his intensive 
efforts with all the parties concerned with the crisis, the UN 
Security Council member states, and the UN secretary general to 
work for implementation of Resolution 924. 
  The Arab League expressed regret for the noncompliance with 
the appeals for a cease-fire, affirming that it is necessary to 
stop the fighting in order to begin an effective dialogue to 
resolve the current Yemeni crisis. 

</TEXT>

