<H3> <TI>   Musa Denies Yemeni Meeting To Be Held in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Denies Yemeni Meeting To Be Held in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1806140794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1453 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1806140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 18 Jun (MENA) -- Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
has denied that a meeting between the Yemeni parties will be 
held in Cairo tomorrow, Sunday. 
  In a statement he made today, he said that UN envoy to Yemen 
Lakhdar Ibrahimi will leave Cairo for New York tomorrow and that 
there are no agreement on any specific proposals or steps. 
  Musa added that what Egypt is demanding and insisting on is 
a 
cease-fire and the disengagement of forces in Yemen. 
  He stressed that the opportunities for protecting Yemen's 
unity will decrease the longer the fighting continues. 
  Regarding the situation in Rwanda, Musa said that the United 
Nations has decided to send troops there, and noted that France 
has also taken an initiative on this issue. He added that Egypt 
is bound by whatever the African countries decide. 

</TEXT>

